g.text: If suspicious of infection refer to Sepsis Screening Tool
The patient is fully alertThe patient is exhibiting new confusionThe patient responds to verbal stimulation The patient responds to painful stimulation The patient is completely unresponsive

Record patient information overleaf, and score each vital sign.A complete vital sign set (oxygen saturation, respiratory rate, temperature, consciousness level, blood pressure, and heart rate) must be recorded at intervals no less than those stated in the escalation pathway.Add the individual scores to find the TOTAL SCORE and follow the escalation pathway.
